<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Students</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/students.css">
    <style>
        /* Add your CSS styles for the tabs here */
        .tab-button {
    display: flex;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    margin-right: 5px;
    border-radius: 5px;
    position: relative; /* Add this to make the ::after pseudo-element positioned relative to the button */
}

.tab-button::after {
    content: "\f107"; /* Unicode for the down arrow icon (you can replace this with your preferred arrow icon) */
    font-family: FontAwesome; /* Use a font icon library like FontAwesome or replace with an arrow image */
    margin-left: 5px; /* Add some space between the button text and arrow */
    transition: transform 0.3s; /* Add a smooth transition for the arrow rotation */
}

.tab-button.active::after {
  content: "\f106"; 
    transform: rotate(180deg); /* Rotate the arrow 180 degrees when the button is active */
}

        .tab-content {
            display: flex;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            margin-top: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('templates/header-1.ejs') -%>

    <div class="block">
        <!-- Create tab buttons -->
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('eligibility')">Eligibility Criteria</div>
        
        <!-- Create tab content for each section -->
        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="eligibility">
            <!-- Content for Eligibility Criteria section -->
            <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>All students expecting to graduate from the institute by the end of the academic year 2023 - 2024 and seeking employment are eligible.</li>
                <li>Each student must complete online registration through the Placement Cell's designated forum, such as Superset, Google Forms, etc., by uploading a properly formatted resume and paying the registration fees.</li>
                <li>Students with three or more course backlogs upon completing semester 6/8/2 for BTech, Dual Degree, MTech, and respective programs are ineligible for placement registration. However, if a student successfully clears excess backlogs by the 7/9/3 semester, they will be allowed to register for placements.</li>
                <li>Students who have lost their job for genuine reasons will be permitted to re-register on a case-by-case basis. Re-registration will be allowed only for students with a course extension or other valid reasons.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('responsibility')">Student Responsibility</div>

        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="responsibility">
            <!-- Content for Student Responsibility section -->
            <h2>Student Responsibility</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Information about company visits will be communicated through email, notice boards, the institute's website, Superset, and Telegram groups (referred to as communication channels). Students are advised to stay updated with announcements, review company websites, and apply only if genuinely interested.</li>
                <li>Students are expected to adhere to the resume template provided on the placement website when preparing their resumes.</li>
                <li>The information in the resume must be accurate, and any student found providing false information will be prohibited from applying for placements for the remainder of the academic year.</li>
                <li>Depending on the profile and requirements specified by the respective company, a comprehensive resume must be prepared and submitted within the deadline. Late submissions will not be considered for tests or interviews.</li>
                <li>It is the student's responsibility to check announcements, notices, updated information, shortlisted names, etc., on notice boards, via email, on the website, and through communication channels. Students must report to the designated venue as per the announcements.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('interaction')">Pre-Placement Interaction</div>

        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="interaction">
            <!-- Content for Pre-Placement Interaction section -->
            <h2>Pre-Placement Interaction</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Only students who have submitted their resumes and attended the Pre-Placement Interaction (PPI) session are eligible to participate in the selection process of the respective company. Attendance at PPI sessions is mandatory.</li>
                <li>Students must use the PPI sessions to clarify any queries they have regarding salary breakdown, job profile, work location, bond details, medical fitness requirements, and other relevant matters with company officials.</li>
                <li>Questions about the pay package offered by the company are not permitted, and students shall not question the company's policies during the interaction.</li>
                <li>Interactions with company representatives should be conducted with dignity and respect.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('attendance')">Attendance and Punctuality</div>

        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="attendance">
            <!-- Content for Attendance and Punctuality section -->
            <h2>Attendance and Punctuality</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Latecomers for the Aptitude Test, Group Discussion, or Interview may be denied the opportunity to participate in the selection process.</li>
                <li>Once a student applies and is shortlisted, they are expected to complete the entire selection process unless rejected by the recruiter midway.</li>
                <li>Any student who deliberately withdraws during a selection process will be disqualified from placement opportunities for the remainder of the academic year.</li>
                <li>Unauthorized absence from the test or interview will result in the cancellation of registration.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('dresscode')">Dress Code</div>

        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="dresscode">
            <!-- Content for Dress Code section -->
            <h2>Dress Code</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Students must dress formally for any interaction with a company. The coordinator has the authority to deny permission to students with unsatisfactory attire. The dress code applies to Pre-placement talks as well.</li>
                <li>Boys should wear formal dark pants with a light-colored full-sleeve shirt, a necktie, and formal shoes.</li>
                <li>Girls should wear Churidar, Salwar, Shirt-Pant with an overcoat, and formal shoes.</li>
                <li>Students must carry their identity cards when participating in any placement process.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('joboffers')">Job Offers</div>
        
        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="joboffers">
            <!-- Content for Job Offers section -->
            <h2>Job Offers</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Announcements on the notice board, via email, or on the website will be considered as the final job offer. Students must collect job offers as per the timings specified in the circular or notice.</li>
                <li>Students should refrain from questioning why they were not selected by a company. The selection process is solely at the discretion of the company. Any unruly behavior that compromises the institute's reputation will render the student ineligible for future internship procedures and subject to disciplinary action.</li>
                <li>It is the student's responsibility to thoroughly review the offer letter and take appropriate actions, such as document submission.</li>
                <li>Students should respond to job offers and communicate with the industry in a respectful and professional manner.</li>
                <li>If students receive job offers directly from a company, they must inform the placement office.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('multipleoffers')">Multiple Job Offers</div>
    
        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="multipleoffers">
            <!-- Content for Multiple Job Offers section -->
            <h2>Multiple Job Offers</h2>
            <h4>Eligibility to apply for second campus offer</h4>
            <li>No student is eligible for a second job offer.</li>

            <h4>In case receiving two campus offers</h4>
            <li>If a student receives more than one offer owing to delays in the announcement of results by the recruiters, he/she is bound to accept the job whose results are declared first.</li>
            <li>If the results are declared on the same day, the student may choose from the offers in hand and inform the placement coordinator within 2 days of the announcement of the results.</li>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('joiningstatus')">Joining Status</div>
     
        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="joiningstatus" style="display: none;">
            <!-- Content for Joining Status section -->
            <h2>Joining Status</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Students should notify the company with a copy to the placement office in case they are not joining the company for reasons.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-button" onclick="showTab('notcovered')">Issues not covered</div>

        <div class="tab-content" style="display: none;" id="notcovered">
            <!-- Content for Issues not covered section -->
            <h2>Issues not covered</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>For all matters not covered by the mentioned regulations, the placement coordinators will use their discretion to take appropriate decisions. Feel free to ask any doubts or questions regarding any of the points mentioned here for the placement procedure.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Add more tab content sections for other sections -->
    </div>

    <%- include('templates/footer-1.ejs') -%>

    <script>
        // JavaScript function to show/hide tab content
        function showTab(tabId) {
        const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
        tabs.forEach(tab => {
            tab.style.display = 'none';
        });

        const selectedTab = document.getElementById(tabId);
        if (selectedTab.style.display === 'none' || selectedTab.style.display === '') {
            selectedTab.style.display = 'block';
        }
         else if(selectedTab.style.display === 'block') {
            selectedTab.style.display = 'none';
        }
    }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
